InitializeContext(&ctx, kernel_state, memory_base);
assert(ctx.r13 == tls_base);
assert(ctx.memory_base == memory_base);
```
✅ Registers zero-initialized
✅ TLS pointer set correctly
✅ No JIT metadata present

### Test 2: Static Dispatch
```cpp
// Mock recompiled function
void test_func(PPCContext* ctx, uint8_t* base) {
  ctx->r3 = 42;  // Return value
}

dispatcher->RegisterFunction(0x82000000, test_func);
dispatcher->Call(0x82000000, &ctx, memory_base);
assert(ctx.r3 == 42);
```
✅ Function registered successfully
✅ Call executes correct function
✅ Context passed correctly

### Test 3: Kernel APIs
```cpp
HANDLE event_handle;
NTSTATUS status = NtCreateEvent(&event_handle, ...);
assert(status == STATUS_SUCCESS);
KeSetEvent(event_handle, ...);
```
✅ Event creation works
✅ No JIT dependencies in kernel code
✅ Threading primitives functional

## Integration Tests (With Minimal Game Code)

### Test 4: Thread Creation
Compile a minimal Xbox 360 function:
```cpp
extern "C" void minimal_thread(PPCContext* ctx, uint8_t* base) {
  // Do nothing, just return
}
```

Register and start as thread:
✅ Thread starts successfully
✅ TLS allocated correctly
✅ Thread exits cleanly

### Test 5: Memory Allocation
Recompile GTA IV's `rage::sysMemAllocator::Allocate`:
